# Effect API Layer (`apps/web/src/api`)

## Client

`base/client.ts` — `fetch` + Bearer token from `authToken`, returns `Effect.Effect<T, ApiError>`.

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — typed Effect pipeline
httpClient.get<unknown>('/task').pipe(
  Effect.flatMap(Schema.decodeUnknown(TaskSchema))
)
```

## BaseApiService

Extend for new entities:

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — apps/web/src/api/taskApi.ts pattern
class TaskApi extends BaseApiService<Task> {
  constructor() {
    super('task', TaskSchema as Schema.Schema<Task, unknown>)
  }
}
export const taskApi = new TaskApi()
```

## Schemas

Define in `types/schema.ts` with `effect` `Schema.Struct`. Match API camelCase JSON.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — separate @effect/schema package
import { Schema } from '@effect/schema'

// ✅ GOOD
import { Schema } from 'effect'
```

## Auth API

`authApi.ts` uses `runRequest` for Promise-based stores; entity APIs can stay Effect-native in components/stores.

Endpoint paths: `/auth/login`, `/auth/register`, `/auth/me` (no leading duplication — `BASE_URL` already ends with `/api`).
